The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for the localization of chest pathologies in X-ray images. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves the use of class-aware feature learning, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of multiscale feature maps and attention maps also involves the manipulation of multimedia data (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves the use of image retrieval techniques for pathology classification, which falls under the domain of information retrieval (cs.IR).
